parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall without warning, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents. Additionally, faulty ignition switches can cause electrical system malfunctions, potentially leading to fires.
symptoms: the ignition switch does not return to its normal position
the ignition switch requires banging or wiggling to start the vehicle
sparks are visible around the steering column
accessories such as headlights do not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can compromise the safety of occupants in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle will not stay buckled
the spring latch fails to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A vehicle fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle, pose a risk to the occupants and bystanders, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: often while parked or in operation
with no warning signs or symptoms.
